org.apache.taverna.configuration

Interface Configurable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    HttpProxyConfiguration
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConfigurable, HttpProxyConfigurationImpl

    public interface Configurable
    An interface that defines an Object as being configurable. It supports the core properties that allows this items configuration to be stored and re-populated by the ConfigurationManager

      • getInternalPropertyMap

        Map<String,String> getInternalPropertyMap()
        Provides access to the internal map.
        Note that this map may contain internal identifiers for deleted entries for deleted values that also have corresponding default values. For this reason using this map directly is discouraged, and #getProperty(String)} should be used instead.
        Returns:

      • setProperty

        void setProperty(String key,
                 String value)
        Overwrites or applies a new value against the given key in the property map.
        Setting a value to null is equivalent to calling thisdeleteProperty(String)
        If the value is new, or changed, the the property map is stored.
        Using this method is preferable to using the property map directly.
